eferred direction for bond motion using the stress tensor corresponds to\nthe most compressible direction and not to the least compressible direction as\npreviously reported. We show the necessity for a directional approach\nconstructed using the eigenvectors along the entire bond length and demonstrate\nthe insufficiency of the sole use of scalar measures for capturing the nature\nof the stress tensor within the QTAIM partitioning.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Sep 2018 23:05:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-19"}
